x=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.undeadart.com/forum/alucard.gif width=100 height=94></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Castlevania: White Night Concerto</span><hr size=1> I don't understand why they're naming it that... Not only does it screw up the name pattern (Symphony of the Night, Circle of the Moon), but it doesn't make any sense. The title is a contradiction. <p><table width=100% border=0><tr><td>Thomas Bonvillain<br><img src=http://www.undeadart.com/temp/banner/banner.gif><a href=http://www.undeadart.com>undeadart.com</a></td><td><a href=http://pkimage.dhs.org/crit/crit.htm>Click here</a> for a broken link!<br><br></td><tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uthezerosamurai.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Zero Samurai</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Xaithian</span><br> <font color=#336699>(6/14/02 2:51:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=217.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.marua.com/zerosamurai/FinalMoment0042.gif height=140 width=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Castlevania: White Night Concerto</span><hr size=1> I don't name 'em, I just report about it.  Myself, I am happy to see that they may have a decent series going here on the GBA.  That crazy little system is a whole new life for side-scrolling Castlevania games. <p><br><br><br><br><br><B>You may say I'm a dreamerBut I'm not the only oneI hope someday you'll join usAnd the world will be as one</B></br>-- <I>Imagine</I></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ualucard1515.showPublicProfile?language=EN>alucard1515</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator <img src=http://contest.polykarbon.com/badge1.gif></span><br> <font color=#336699>(6/15/02 12:12:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=217.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.undeadart.com/forum/alucard.gif width=100 height=94></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Castlevania: White Night Concerto</span><hr size=1> Hopefully it's better than the last one. Not that it was bad, just that some of the changes they made from Symphony of the Night made the game less fun. The card system was interesting, but it only let you use ONE of those abilities at a time. There were equivalent abilities you had in SOTN like weapons, familiars, spells, etc that you could do all at once. I never even used most of the card combinations that often because they weren't nearly as useful as other abilities. <p><table width=100% border=0><tr><td>Thomas Bonvillain<br><img src=http://www.undeadart.com/temp/banner/banner.gif><a href=http://www.undeadart.com>undeadart.com</a></td><td><a href=http://pkimage.dhs.org/crit/crit.htm>Click here</a> for a broken link!<br><br></td><tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/umercurialme.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mercurial Me</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(6/18/02 7:37:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=217.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.liquid2k.com/anyte/misc/ajigumi2.jpg x-114 y=114></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Castlevania: White Night Concerto</span><hr size=1> I'm a whee bit disappointed.  I don't think it's as good.  At some points it's just way too easy.  It's hard to give an opinion on the items since I don't even know what half of them are or what they do (it's all in Japanese), but a couple of them are kinda fun.  <br><br>I'm only 40% through and I am actually stuck, but that could easily be fixed by going back and leveling up a bit. <p><br><br><center><font size=2><a href="http://pub80.ezboard.com/umercurialme.showPublicProfile">New profile!</a>   <font color=red>I'm FUN.   <a href="aim:goim?Screenname=anyterenee">Lets's CHAT d00d.  =)</a>   I'm FUN.  <a href="http://www.liquid2k.com/anyte">Webby!</a></font></center><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/upazka.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pazka</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.zeldagames.com/pics/oni2.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(6/18/02 9:46:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=217.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/dogfuchow/pazka.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Castlevania: White Night Concerto</span><hr size=1> I heard the game was going to be better than circle of the mooon.  Frankly I can't wait for it to come out.  I saw some screen shots of it and they look really good.  I heard when it's done the graphics are supposed to be better than last time.  I think they might be bringing back the car system too.  Which is good and bad.<br><br>Mercurial me what game are you talking about? <p>------------- <b><i>Being a tiger is more than just stripes               -Hobbes</i></b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ualucard1515.showPublicProfile?language=EN>alucard1515</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator <img src=http://contest.polykarbon.com/badge1.gif></span><br> <font color=#336699>(6/18/02 11:54:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=217.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.undeadart.com/forum/alucard.gif width=100 height=94></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Castlevania: White Night Concerto</span><hr size=1> I just read that the team that did SOTN is doing this game, and it will be longer and have more spells and weapons than the last one. Good, because that was the main problem with the last one. <p><table width=100% border=0><tr><td>Thomas Bonvillain<br><img src=http://www.undeadart.com/temp/banner/banner.gif><a href=http://www.undeadart.com>undeadart.com</a></td><td><a href=http://pkimage.dhs.org/crit/crit.htm>Click here</a> for a broken link!<br><br></td><tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uspyders17.showPublicProfile?language=EN>spyders17</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(6/18/02 1:37:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=217.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.liquid2k.com/spyder17/luciferavatar2.gif width=125 height=115></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Castlevania: White Night Concerto</span><hr size=1> I just saw some screenshots of the game on gameforms.com...and I sure hope they don't do the game any justice, cuz i personally think CotM's graphics suit the castlevania mood a lot better, the new seems so bright and colorful, it just kinda bothers me.<br><br>and I don't mind the darkness, I can almost always find a good enough spot to play CotM (and I'm gonna get the afterburner anyways)<br><br>but ya, other than that, it looks like a good game, and is, from what I've heard, can't compare it to